106. Ad summam .·] This is an ordinary formula, ‘ to come to the point,' ‘to conclude! The pursuit of virtue and wisdom is the point from which he started, and, having digressed a little, he returns suddenly, and concludes with a definition of the sege, which is a repetition of S. i. 3. 124, sqq.
